Sweet Corn Spoonbread
  --Cook's country

1 c cornmeal
2 3/4 c whole milk
4 tbsp unsalted butter
2 c corn kernels (3-4 ears of corn, can sub frozen as long as it's fully thawed & drained)
1 tsp sugar
1 tsp salt
1/8 tsp cayenne
3 large eggs, separated
1/4 tsp cream of tartar

Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 400F. Grease 1 1/2 qt souffle dish or 8" square baking dish. Whisk cornmeal and 3/4 c milk in bowl until combined; set aside. Melt butter in dutch oven over medium high heat. Cook corn until beginning to brown, ~3 min. Stir in remaining milk, sugar, salt, and cayenne and bring to boil. Remove from heat, cover, and let mixture steep 15 min. Transfer warm corn mixture to blender or food processor and puree until smooth. Return corn mixture to pot and bring to boil. Reduce heat to low and add cornmeal mixture, whisking constantly, until thickened, 2-3 min; transfer to large bowl and cool to room temp, ~20 min. Once mixture is cool, whisk in yolks until combined. With electric mixer on medium low speed, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy, ~1 min. Increase speed to medium high and beat until stiff peaks form, ~3 min. Whisk 1/3 of whites into corn mixture, then gently fold in remaining whites until combined. Scrape mixture into prepared dish and transfer to oven. Reduce temp to 350F and bake until golden brown and risen above rim of dish, ~45 min. Serve immediately.

To make individual, divide baatter among 6 greased 7 oz ramekins. Arrange ramekins on rimmed baking sheet and bake as directed, reducing cook time to 30-35 min.
